participating-org.narrative:
The FOPABU is a non-political Organization established on July 19; 2009 and approved by Ministerial Order n ° 530/1757 of 29/10/2012 In the beginning, it was created by 6 producer organizations including CNAC; CAPAD; CAPRI; APROPABU; CNAPCO-GIRISHAKA; CNATHE-NYAMUKAMIGWABOSE Currently FOPABU totals 11 Producers Organizations, and hope that the number of its members will go on increasing because of statutes are open to all PO

The vision of FOPABU "farmers have become true professionals, capable to defend their socio-economic and sustainable interests, and to ensure their food security and sovereignty."

The missions of FOPABU #strengthen the PO capacity and influence agricultural laws and policies to professionalize agricultural producers with a viewto food security and sovereignty in Burundi".

FOPABU values: solidarity, integrity, commitment, professionalism and governance

Practice areas
 Agricultural policy advocacy;
 Defending the interests of farmers;
 Capacity Building ;
 Coordinatingother actors of civil society working in the agricultural sector through the GPA.
Institutional goals
a. Gather all the organizations of agricultural producers in a single week;
b. Ensure representation and advocacy for rural development;
c. Defend therights and interests of organizations member;
d. Be actively involved in the monitoring of policies and programs to improve the living conditions
e. Contributing to provide information for the development of rural areas;
f. Be interested in anythingthat can contribute to the promotion of agriculture in all its aspects;
g. Advocating that development programs take into account environmental aspects.
